There is a very simple proposition which throws much light on this difficult matter—and needless to say that this doctrine of Jesus is difficult‚ and can only be grasped by faith. Let us clearly hold in mind that love that is less than lik- ing is not love. If, then, we love our enemies and sinners, it must be by a genuine liking for all that it is possible to like in them, which cannot be found out without companionship and some community of interest.
